paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted genetic variant information for the TTR gene, including penetrance data.

patients.phenotype: ATTRv patients presented more frequently with bilateral CTS and autonomic dysfunction, followed by ataxia, unexplained weight loss, and cardiomyopathy.

functional_data.summary: The most frequent mutations encountered were Phe64Leu (52%), Val30Met (31%), Glu89Gln (5%), and Val122Ile (3%).

variants.additional_notes: The study included a cohort of 93 mutated ATTRv probands.
key_quotes: Among ATTRv patients, the most frequent mutations encountered were Phe64Leu (52%), Val30Met (31%), Glu89Gln (5%), and Val122Ile (3%).

tables_processed.table_caption: Clinical characteristics of patients with positive and negative genetic testing.

extraction_metadata.notes: The extraction focused solely on the TTR gene variants as specified.
